.TH MFUTIL-REORGANIZE 1 2025-01-01 "mfutil 0.1.1"
.SH NAME
mfutil-reorganize \- Reorganize misplaced music files
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mfutil reorganize
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B reorganize
subcommand finds music files that are not in their proper artist/album
directory structure and moves them to the correct location based on their metadata.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-music-dir " " \fIPATH\fR
Specify the music directory path (default: ~/Music)
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information
.SH OPERATION
Scans the music directory for audio files outside the standard Artists/Artist/Album
structure and relocates them to the appropriate directories based on embedded metadata.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Reorganize misplaced files in default music directory:
.B mfutil reorganize
.TP
Reorganize misplaced files in custom directory:
.B mfutil reorganize --music-dir /path/to/music
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mfutil (1),
.BR mfutil-organize (1),
.BR mfutil-all (1)
.SH WARNING
This command moves files. While it attempts to preserve data integrity,
it's recommended to backup your music library before running.